<Author>Keemer54
<Content>Great hotel This is a lovely hotel with very helpful, professional, friendly staff. It's slightly off the main road in an area that seems to be mostly offices (and the German Interior Ministry building, complete with police presence), so felt very safe indeed. There are a couple of lovely restaurants on the same block, which is great for when you've just arrived or if you don't feel like venturing into the city of an evening. The 'Lanninger' bar looks out onto the Spree and some lovely buildings opposite, with seating on the riverbank for warm evenings. The hotel does cycle hire, which I'd recommend; Berlin is as flat as a pancake and with the cycle paths you can't go wrong. Riding around the Tiergarten on a sunny day was just great. The hotel is also handy for bus and U-bahn stops. The room was clean, modern and spacious, and had air conditioning. The beds were comfortable and there was plenty of room for hanging clothes. I would definitely go back to this hotel. 
