<Author>AvidReader8
<Content>Solid room but DRILLING from 8-5 every day!! Nice hotel, tucked away down a side street. AMAZING breakfast buffet every day of the week. Room was standard, but gets high marks for lots of surfaces and shelves, good lighting and a good bed. Heat didn't work in our room 2 of the 3 nights. They are remodeling and put us on the floor nearest the drilling or jackhammering. Here's the catch-22: we were too worn out from fighting the tension of hearing the drilling to pack up and change rooms. Ditto for another couple in our group. Can't imagine why they would place any guest near that noise. They get terrible marks for neglecting to attend to a quality guest experience. If you want to book here, check first to see if any renovations are going on. It has potential, if they put you in a quiet room and if the heat works. The staff had a somewhat disdainful attitude. 
