<Author>Eliska_1
<Content>Nice hotel, BUT be aware of the beds We stayed in the Spreebogen Berlin for two nights. The hotel is very nice, clean, staff is very friendly, the breakfast is one of the better ones I had. The only thing which doesn't make this hotel top is their beds. They're absolutely dreadful. Very bouncy so if it's two of you on double/king bed every time one person moves the other one does as well... If you travel to Berlin via car, the hotel is quite close to the Main train station and it's well hidden on the Alt Moabit Street. It's by a river, but in a courtyard!! So we drove past couple of times before we found it. The hotel doesn't have own parking lot, so you have to use a public parking (which is underneath the hotel) and will cost you 1.20EUR per hour or 17.50 EUR per 24 hours.This hotel is about 25 minutes walk from the Brandenburg gate; about 40 minutes walk from the Check point Charlie so I recommend you use the public transport. But overall Berlin is a great city and I'm sure you all will have a good time! 
